25|$|In thermodynamics, an <b>adiabatic</b> <b>process</b> is {{a change}} that occurs without heat flow, and slowly {{compared}} to the time to reach equilibrium. In an <b>adiabatic</b> <b>process,</b> the system is in equilibrium at all stages. Under these conditions, the entropy is constant.|$|E
