2500|$|The Nernst {{postulate}} {{identifies the}} isotherm T=0 as coincident with the adiabat S=0, although other isotherms and adiabats are distinct. As no two adiabats intersect, no other adiabat can intersect the T=0 isotherm. Consequently no <b>adiabatic</b> <b>process</b> initiated at nonzero temperature {{can lead to}} zero temperature. (≈Callen, pp.189–190) ...|$|E
